==English==
===Etymology===
From [[white]] + [[list]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-whitelist.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''whitelist'''
#A [[list]] or collection of [[people]] or [[entities]] that are known, trusted, or explicitly permitted.

===Verb===
'''whitelist'''
#To place on a whitelist; to mark or note a person or entity as trustworthy or acceptable.
#:''The email program allows you to '''whitelist''' email from known sources.''

